<h3 id="follow-us" sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="159">Follow us</h3>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="161">To customize the <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="161">Follow us</strong> block of the footer, go to <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="161">Configuration → Settings → General settings</strong>. Proceed to the <em sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="161">Social media</em> panel as follows:</p>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="163"><img src="_static/top-menu-and-footer/social-media-settings.jpg" sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="163" alt="Social media settings"></p>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="165">Enter your social media links:</p>
<ul sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="167">
<li sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="167"><strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="167">Facebook page URL</strong></li>
<li sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="168"><strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="168">Twitter page URL</strong></li>
<li sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="169"><strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="169">YouTube channel URL</strong></li>
<li sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="170"><strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="170">Instagram page URL</strong></li>
</ul>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="172">If you want to enable/disable the RSS link in the footer, you need to enable/disable news accordingly on the <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="172">Configuration → Settings → News settings</strong> page (<em sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="172">Common</em> panel).</p>
<h3 id="newsletter" sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="174">Newsletter</h3>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="176">The newsletter block is displayed in the footer by default. To hide this block go to <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="176">Configuration → Settings → Customer settings</strong>. Proceed to the <em sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="176">Account</em> panel and select the <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="176">Hide newsletter box</strong> checkbox as follows:</p>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="178"><img src="_static/top-menu-and-footer/newsletter-settings.jpg" sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="178" alt="Newsletter box settings"></p>
<p sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="180">Click <strong sourcefile="en/getting-started/design-your-store/top-menu-and-footer.md" sourcestartlinenumber="180">Save</strong> to save the changes. The footer will be updated accordingly.</p>
